{
  "texts": [
    "Here, we summarise key UI features that emerged from the included articles:• Giving stakeholders full or greater control over UI features such as which information to be put on display (e.g., recommended actions, amount of information, language) [12,13,63].",
    "• Considering user profiles for the design of size and shape of the UI [63], usability of user login [38], and interfaces concerning position of buttons, colours, alarm tones [38,64].",
    "• Accommodating minority user groups by incorporating settings of user preferences and personalised AI features into UI (e.g., additional features for elderly users to include bigger font size, and a speech interface) [57,64].",
    "• Non-dependency on stable wireless network connection to use AI-enabled systems [64].",
    "• Conducting all tests of AI-enabled systems prior to deploying them to ensure user personalisation [13,38].• Establishing practices to ensure compliance with GDPR [57], and enforcing informed consent to process and share user data and explicitly inform users that they could ask for their data to be deleted at any time [38,49]."
  ]
}